        public Course(int courseID,
      java.lang.String courseName,
      int courseSection,
      java.lang.String courseDays,
      java.lang.String courseTime,
      int courseCapacity,
      Instructor instructor,
      java.lang.String department,
      java.util.ArrayList<Student> enrolledStudents)
        This Constructor is used to create a Course from an entry from a file. A Course that is created in this way already has a Course ID that is read from the file.
        Parameters:
        courseID - The ID number for the Course.
        courseName - The name of the Course.
        courseSection - The section number of the Course.
        courseDays - The days that the Course occurs on.
        courseTime - The time of day that the Course occurs on.
        courseCapacity - The max number of Students the Course can hold.
        instructor - The Instructor of the Course.
        department - The department that offers the Course.
        enrolledStudents - The list of Students that are enrolled in the Course.
